JetBlue is proud to be the ✨ first ✨ airline to accept Venmo for flight bookings. 🎉\\n\\nCustomers can now book their next trip on jetblue.com and pay seamlessly with their Venmo balance, linked debit cards, credit cards, or bank accounts.\\n\\nThis partnership with Venmo makes booking flights even easier and more convenient for our customers. company_updates.description: The entire PayPal team stands with the greater Los Angeles community, and everyone impacted by the devastating wildfires. As the situation continues to unfold, we continue to prioritize the safety and well-being of our employees and aid critical relief and recovery efforts.\\n\\nHere’s how we’re helping those impacted by this tragedy:\\n\\n🔵 Matching up to $1 million USD in customer donations (up to $1,000 USD per user) made to support select charities responding to the disaster through PayPal Giving Fund on our campaign page through February 12, 2025. Contributions to this campaign will aid charitable organizations that are responding to the disaster and providing essential services to the affected communities and first responders. We are also matching 100% of eligible employee donations through an internal employee giving campaign.\\n\\n🔵 Granting a total of $1 million to support the California Community Foundation, the California Fire Foundation, the Los Angeles Regional Food Bank, and the Los Angeles Fire Department Foundation. We also previously contributed to the American Red Cross’s Annual Disaster Giving Program, which has enabled them to quickly activate in the area.\\n\\n🔵 Ensuring that PayPal merchants in the impacted areas have our support in their recovery by offering relief from late fees, collections reporting, and loan repayments.\\n\\nPlease consider donating here: https://lnkd.in/gQiKmbxc\\n\\nThank you to our entire PayPal community for coming together to support our colleagues and communities in need.

That’s why we're proud to announce the 2024 PayPal Community Impact Grant recipients!  \\n\\nThis year, 77 organizations across 22 countries have been selected to receive grant funding, volunteer support from PayPal employees, and pro bono resources. These grants are part of our ongoing commitment to revolutionize commerce globally by expanding economic opportunity for all. \\n\\nEach year, our employees play a pivotal role in this initiative by nominating local nonprofits that align with our mission.
